section.t:
The following examples illustrate how success and failure are
      represented in responses to batch requests. 
      Batch successful, all procedure calls successful:

[
  { 
    "id" : "myself", 
    "result" : { ... }
  },
  { 
    "id" : "myfriends", 
    "result" : { ... }
  }           
]

      Batch successful, some procedure calls successful while some fail:

[
  { 
    "id" : "myself", 
    "result" : { ... }
  },
  { 
    "id" : "myfriends", 
    "error" : { ... }
  }
]

      Batch successful, all procedure calls fail:

[
  { 
    "id" : "myself", 
    "error" : { ... }
  },
  { 
    "id" : "myfriends", 
    "error" : { ... }
  }
]

      Batch fails:

{
  "error" : { ... }
}

